# Cursor Editor Configuration for ValidoAI Project
# GPU Support and Development Optimization        

## GPU Configuration
- Enable GPU acceleration for AI/ML tasks
- Support both NVIDIA CUDA and AMD ROCm
- Optimize for local model inference
- Configure memory management for large models    

## Development Environment
- Use Python 3.12+ with GPU support
- Enable PyTorch CUDA/ROCm acceleration
- Configure TensorFlow GPU support
- Optimize for local AI model development

## Project Structure
- Root: app.py, routes.py, configuration files no scattering of routes
- src/: All Python logic and modules
- docs/: Documentation organized by category (api/, architecture/, guides/, deployment/, security/, tutorials/)
- templates/: HTML templates
- static/: CSS, JS, images
- data/: Database files and sample data
- tests/: All tests organized by type (unit/, integration/, e2e/, performance/, security/)
- configuration_scripts/: All .sh and .ps1 scripts for setup, deployment, and maintenance
- All global desing style is defined in main.{css, js}

## Template Structure Rules
- All routes MUST follow the pattern: /templates/{route-name}/{CRUD}.html
- Examples: /templates/dashboard/index.html, /templates/tickets/create.html, /templates/users/edit.html
- CRUD operations: index.html (list/view), create.html, edit.html, show.html (view single), delete.html
- ALWAYS check for existing files in the route directory before creating new ones
- If existing file found, merge/update the existing file instead of creating duplicates
- Follow the existing file structure and naming conventions
- Each route directory should contain only the necessary CRUD templates
- Base template (base.html) is shared across all routes

## AI/ML Configuration
- Local model management in src/ai_local_models/
- GPU detection and optimization
- Model downloading and caching
- Inference engine with GPU support
- Sample data in /data/sqlite/sample.db

## Database Configuration
- **PostgreSQL Connection Method**: Use PowerShell environment variable
- **Standard Connection Command**:
  ```
  $env:PGPASSWORD = "postgres"
  psql -h localhost -p 5432 -U postgres -d ai_valido_online
  ```
- **Connection Details**:
  - Host: localhost
  - Port: 5432
  - Username: postgres
  - Password: postgres
  - Database: ai_valido_online
- **ALWAYS use the environment variable method** to avoid interactive password prompts
- **NEVER hardcode passwords** in scripts or configuration files
- **Use this exact method** for all database operations and verifications

## Code Style
- Use PowerShell for CRUD on all files, this is faster method
- Follow PEP 8 standards
- Use the best patterns for Python
- Use type hints
- Implement OOP, MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel), MVC, ELM patterns
- DRY principle - no code duplication
- Find and check first code
- Each route has component way of using css, js, images, fonts, icons, etc. is defined in /static/{route-name}/{route-name}.{css,js,image, font, icons, etc.}
- All routes only in routes.py - no routes duplication
- Try to have minimal number of files created
- Don't create new files, try first to change/merge/update current files
- Don't add enhanced and all other variants to the file names
- Don't break the rules please follow them

## Performance
- Enable GPU acceleration where available
- Optimize model loading and inference
- Use efficient data structures
- Implement caching strategies

## Security
- Validate all inputs
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Implement proper error handling
- Secure API endpoints

## Testing
- Test GPU detection and configuration
- Validate model loading and inference
- Test error handling and logging
- Verify route functionality
- All routes and running the application with 0 errors

## 🔍 **Truth Verification Rule**
**MANDATORY**: All status indicators (✅) MUST be verified and tested before marking as complete. No false progress claims allowed.
- **Before marking ✅**: Must run actual tests and verify functionality
- **Before updating progress %**: Must validate all claimed features work
- **Before claiming "COMPLETED"**: Must demonstrate working functionality
- **Verification Required**: Each completed item must be tested and proven working
- **Automated Testing**: Use verification scripts to validate all claimed features
- **Quality Gates**: Implement mandatory verification before marking features complete
- **Truthful Assessment**: Update progress based on actual verification results
- **Continuous Monitoring**: Maintain ongoing verification system for quality assurance

## 📁 **File Organization Standards**

### **Documentation Organization (/docs)**
- **MANDATORY**: All .md files must be organized in category-based subdirectories
- **Categories**:
  - `/docs/api/` - API documentation and endpoint specifications
  - `/docs/architecture/` - System architecture, database schemas, component diagrams
  - `/docs/guides/` - User guides, tutorials, and how-to documentation
  - `/docs/deployment/` - Deployment guides, Docker configs, production setup
  - `/docs/security/` - Security policies, authentication, data protection
  - `/docs/tutorials/` - Step-by-step tutorials and learning materials
  - `/docs/development/` - Developer guides, coding standards, contribution guidelines

### **Script Organization**
- **MANDATORY**: All .sh and .ps1 scripts must be placed in `/configuration_scripts/`
- **Script Categories**:
  - `setup_*.sh/ps1` - Initial setup and installation scripts
  - `deploy_*.sh/ps1` - Deployment and production scripts
  - `test_*.sh/ps1` - Testing and validation scripts
  - `maintenance_*.sh/ps1` - Database maintenance and cleanup scripts

### **Test Organization**
- **MANDATORY**: All test files must be placed in `/tests/` organized by type:
  - `/tests/unit/` - Unit tests for individual components
  - `/tests/integration/` - Integration tests for system interactions
  -   - `/tests/functional/` - functional tests for all routes
  - `/tests/e2e/` - End-to-end tests for user workflows
  - `/tests/performance/` - Performance and load testing
  - `/tests/routes/` - Status testing for all routes have and return 200 OK no errors on the page
  - `/tests/security/` - Security testing and vulnerability checks

### **Component Organization**
- **All reusable components must be in `/templates/components/`**
- **Component Types**:
  - `modals.html` - Modal dialogs and popups
  - `toasts.html` - Notification toasts
  - `captcha.html` - CAPTCHA components
  - `datatable.html` - Data table components
  - `ckeditor.html` - Rich text editor component
  - `{component-name}.html` - Specific component implementations

## 🔧 **Automation Rules**

### **File Creation**
- **Documentation**: Automatically categorize and place in appropriate `/docs` subdirectories
- **Scripts**: Automatically move .sh/.ps1 files to `/configuration_scripts`
- **Tests**: Automatically organize tests in appropriate `/tests` subdirectories

### **Code Generation**
- **CRUD Templates**: Automatically generate CRUD templates following established patterns
- **API Endpoints**: Generate consistent API endpoint structures
- **Component Structure**: Maintain consistent component architecture

## 📊 **Quality Standards**

### **DRY Principle Enforcement**
- **No Code Duplication**: Use components, utilities, and shared functions
- **Template Inheritance**: Use base templates and includes
- **Component Reuse**: Create reusable components for common UI patterns
- **Utility Functions**: Centralize common operations in utility modules

### **Documentation Standards**
- **Markdown Format**: All documentation must use consistent markdown
- **Table of Contents**: Required for documents > 50 lines
- **Cross-References**: Use relative links between documentation files
- **Version Control**: Maintain changelog for major updates

